<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RODMAN'S STATUS REMAINS UNCERTAIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO _ Worm Watch '99, interrupted by a brief, nine-game
appearance by Dennis Rodman, has returned as the Los Angeles
Lakers' favorite pastime.
</P>
<P>
   They watched and waited for three weeks for Rodman to sign, the
anticipation ending with a contract and a nine-game winning streak
with him on the roster. Now he's missing again, with no sign when
he'll return.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman skipped practice Saturday, then informed the team he
would not be joining them on their six-game road trip, at least not
yet. By Sunday, the team was no closer to knowing when or if he'll
be back.
</P>
<P>
   ``He said he would be back,'' coach Kurt Rambis said, but for
this six-game road trip, no one knows.
</P>
<P>
   Team spokesman John Black indicated the absence was excused _
``You could phrase it that way'' _ and that Rodman was being paid
for Sunday's game. Black said team executives had spoken with
Rodman's agent but he was uncertain whether anyone had spoken to
Rodman himself.
</P>
<P>
   The team is already moving on.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody else just has to step up,'' Shaquille O'Neal said.
</P>
<P>
   He shrugged off Rodman's disappearance, allowing that whatever
``personal business'' Rodman said he had to attend to was
necessary.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if that's OK with me,'' O'Neal said, ``but I
ain't got time to worry about things I can't control. It's Kurt's
job to do whatever. ... We'll be fine. We've got J.R. (Reid), we've
got another thug (power forward), we ain't trippin'. We straight.
As long as he (Rodman) is there for the playoffs and the big dance
time.''
</P>
<P>
   Rambis figures if Rodman needs the time off, maybe it's for the
best that he takes it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still believe that if players are happy, they're gonna play
better,'' he said. ``Whether they've got business problems or
personal problems, if you can allow them time to get rid of those
problems, they're going to be a lot better off on the court.
</P>
<P>
   ``We all want him as a person to feel good about himself,
whatever that takes. Regardless of what he does with us, that's
just the right thing to do.... But basketball-wise, we have jobs to
do. Whether he's here or not here, we still have to go out on the
floor and produce.''
</P>
<P>
   Ouch report: Derek Harper's sprained left ankle, suffered Friday
night, knocked him out of the game, leaving the Lakers with just 10
players in uniform.
</P>
<P>
   Harper's status remains day-to-day, but he'll have another two
full days to recuperate before the Lakers play again, Tuesday night
at Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   ``We feel that Derek is going to be back soon,'' Rambis said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
