   SAFIRE-COLUMN (Washington) _ ``Absolutely no truth to it _ it's
an outrageous statement,'' fumed Sandy Berger, the first national
security adviser to regularly attend political campaign meetings in
the White House. He was responding to my assertion of connections
among: (a) the Clinton-Gore fund raising from admittedly illegal
Asian sources, followed by our stunning turnabout in trade policy;
