<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-KIDS16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Young reviewer not enchanted by this 'Fairy Tale'
 &HT;    By Yusuf Davis
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The ``Fairy Tale'' activity center wasn't magical for Laura
Thompson of Marietta. The 11-year-old software reviewer stopped
just short of calling the CD-ROM program boring and confessed it
didn't hold her attention for very long.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was OK,'' she said, being generous. ``It just wasn't
great.''
</P>
<P>
   Laura said the fairy-themed activity program was less than
entertaining and didn't capture her imagination. She said she's
unlikely to use the software again.
</P>
<P>
   ``Fairy Tale'' promotes itself as a true-story-come-to-life, in
which kids can experience the enchanting world of fairies and
fantasy. Set against a tropical background with realistic forest
sounds, the program is filled with fairy trivia, puzzles, word
games and numerous magical activities.
</P>
<P>
   At the heart of the activity center are 17 video clips,
featuring two little girls who believe in fairies and try to
convince others (probably adults) that fairies exist.
</P>
<P>
   None of that worked for Laura.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just didn't get it,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   The program also features an interactive 3-D garden and a way
for kids to create sets for their very own fairy tale adventure.
</P>
<P>
   That, too, escaped Laura, who said she didn't see any choices of
interest.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maybe if I had worked harder at it, I would have come up with
something nice,'' Laura said. ``But there were none that I really
liked.''
</P>
<P>
   Because the program didn't interest her much, Laura didn't
explore all of the ``numerous magical activities'' that the program
boasted.
</P>
<P>
   The only segment that was remotely interesting to her was the
quiz that followed each video clip, but even that fell short for
this bright reviewer.
</P>
<P>
   ``That part was pretty fun, but it was way too easy,'' she said.
``Maybe it would have been fun for someone younger.''
</P>
<P>
   'FAIRY TALE: A TRUE STORY ACTIVITY CENTER'
</P>
<P>
   Developer: Knowledge Adventure
</P>
<P>
   Price: $29.95
</P>
<P>
   Format: PC and Mac
</P>
<P>
   Laura's grade: C
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
