<DOCNO> NYT19990315.0141 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 11:03 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0676 &Cx1f; tad-z
r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TECH-REPORT16-COX     03-15 0659
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-REPORT16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TECH BRIEFS: Tending to business from the beyond
 &HT;    By Mark Clothier
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A St. Louis company has come up with the software program for
the ultimate control freak.
</P>
<P>
   PreNeed funeral planning software lets you make your own funeral
arrangements, from choosing a funeral director to picking the hue
of your headstone. The program, which retails for $39, is billed as
the first funeral planning product for the PC.
</P>
<P>
   The Windows-based program creates the PreNeed Plan, divided into
two areas: picking the cemetery, entombment and cremation; and
funeral services and merchandise.
</P>
<P>
   The program starts at the end, covering the issue of where to
place the remains. From there, topics covered include organ or body
donations. If organ donation is your wish, the manual that comes
with the floppy disc lists an address to request a Uniform Donor
Card.
</P>
<P>
   Next the program suggests choosing a burial site.
</P>
<P>
   If a cemetery is the place for you, the folks at Power Solutions
for Business recommend paying in advance, since cemetery costs tend
to double every 10 years. Once a site is chosen, you need to pick a
size and factor in cemetery costs, such as fees for opening and
closing the grave, grave liners, decorations, plantings and
maintenance.
</P>
<P>
   One of the more helpful sections covers funeral costs, which can
be surprisingly high. Urns, for example, can run as high as $1,000.
The manual offers a little insight into how casket salespeople
work. The sale of a casket, the manual reads, is where the funeral
director makes a large chunk of his or her money. The manual points
out the less-expensive models usually won't be prominently
displayed, if at all. Casket sellers are required to furnish a
price list when showing product, according to the manual.
</P>
<P>
   One of the final items is cost. According to the manual, funeral
costs climb 4 percent to 6 percent per year, sometimes more.
</P>
<P>
   When you're done, you can print a report that can serve as a
guideline for the family and funeral director to follow.
</P>
<P>
   Camcorder digital photos
</P>
<P>
   Panasonic has launched what it claims to be the first camcorder
with the ability to take still digital photos.
</P>
<P>
   The Panasonic PV-L759 and PV-L859 use the SanDisk CompactFlash
memory card. The cards are used in more than 140 products,
including digital cameras, hand-held PCs, audio recorders and photo
printers.
</P>
<P>
   The Panasonic camcorders will come with a 2-megabyte memory
card. The feature will let users download images from the camcorder
on the memory card and then move them to a color printer or a PC to
look at or attach to e-mail, Web sites documents or sales
presentations. The cards will hold more than 60 standard resolution
or 15 high-resolution photos.
</P>
<P>
   The camcorders have a suggested retail prices starting at about
$800.
</P>
<P>
   SanDisk, which makes flash data storage products, is based in
Sunnyvale, Calif. The company's site on the Web is
http://www.sandisk.com.
</P>
<P>
   The defense rests
</P>
<P>
   http://www.nolo.com is a Web site for the do-it-yourself lawyer.
</P>
<P>
   Rated the No. 1 legal site on the Web by Yahoo!, nolo.com is a
collection of legal resources. Included is an update on new
copyright laws, tips for being a successful landlord and consumer
rights, which include what to know about your rights as car renter.
</P>
<P>
   The site offers special links, including ones for parents and
children, spouses and partners, and small-business owners.
</P>
<P>
   A legal dictionary is available, as is a store at which you can
buy books and a site from which you can download software.
</P>
<P>
   Some people might not be willing to take the law in their own
hands. But at the very least, the site offers a decent compilation
of lawyer jokes. Sample: How does a pregnant woman know she's
carrying a future lawyer? She has an extreme craving for baloney.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
