<HEADER>
A0693 &Cx1f; tad-z
u k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-COMMENTARY-BJT16-COX     03-15 0332
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, March 16, 1999 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Now we have to hope the Clinton administration,
still dully treating Cuba as if the Cold War never ended, will
somehow begin fine-tuning our Iranian policy to take advantage of,
and help reinforce, the remarkable shift toward moderation there.
(Teepen, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ A recent column opposing school vouchers
produced _ or provoked, as the case may be _ an outpouring of
e-mail. Here's a sampling from here, there and yonder. (Murray, Cox
News Service) MOVED FRIDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Payton is 13 and he has a
problem. ``I'm short, Ms. Schuett,'' he complained one day after
class. I didn't tell him I'd already noticed that. ``I'm never
going to grow any more because I smoked some cigarettes when I was
8. It was my cousin's idea. He's short too.'' (Elizabeth Schuett, a
teacher and writer in Gibsonburg, Ohio, writes twice a week for Cox
News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ I've spent many weekends sitting on
cold metal bleachers at soccer games with icy, gale-force winds
blowing in my face, bemoaning that none of my sons chose to play
basketball or swim _ you know, cozy indoor sports. (Kabat, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ Every
newspaper's oral lore includes at least one story about an
overwrought reporter throwing a typewriter. Maybe out a window.
Maybe at an editor. Technology has changed that. (Lane, Daytona
Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
