new and old music, Bob Wills is still the king in Texas, musicians
say. Even though rock killed his career (despite his claim that he
was rock before Elvis and before it was dubbed that), he was
posthumously inducted Monday (March 15) into the Rock and Roll Hall
of Fame. What does Texas swing have to do with rock 'n' roll?
Wills' daughter lives here, Austin's Asleep atthe Wheel is his
never-ending tribute band and Austinites Al Escovedo and JD Gilmore
recently contributed to a new Wills tribute album featuring a bunch
of punk rockers. Is Bob Wills still the king? And why? (McLeese,
Austin American-Statesman). 40. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
