<P>
   MEDICARE-COMMISSION (Washington) _ Outlines of a plan to save
Medicare take shape as the commission tasked with finding ways to
keep the system going prepares to hold its final meeting Tuesday.
The new plan addresses the two most contentious issues: covering
the cost of prescription drugs and offering beneficiaries the
option of getting a private health insurance plan partly subsidized
by Washington. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   AIRLINES-Y2K (Washington) _ Government investigators now say
they are confident the nation's air traffic control system will
work on Jan. 1. A year ago the Federal Aviation Administration
hadn't started fixing its computers to ensure that they won't
malfunction on or after Jan. 1. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
