was a screenwriter for the TV show ``Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman''
when she fell in love with a cowboy. She was writing a piece on
cowboy poetry for the New York Times Magazine (''Git Along Little
Doggerel'') when a lanky cowpoke in a tan stetson and baby-blue
boots two-stepped off with her heart. She's 50, the divorced mother
of two teen-agers, and he's more than 10 years younger and earns a
meager living braiding rawhide doo-dads, but they're still together
five years later. Now she's written a book, ``Cowboy: A Love
Story,'' about the experience. (Dart, Cox News Service).
