<HEADLINE>
`WATERBOY' ALL OLD GAGS; `BULWORTH' HAS WIT, STYLE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Waterboy'' _ Adam Sandler fans made this
comedy a huge hit in theaters. And they will probably make this
silly story of a football nerd a bigger hit on home video. But I
think it's more for pre-teens and teens than for adults. We've seen
all these gags before.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bulworth'' _ Director-star Warren Beatty had the bad luck to
produce a political satire during a period when no satire could
compete with the real thing. It's a marvelous movie with great wit
and style.
</P>
<P>
   ``101 Dalmatians'' _ The 1961 animated film, not the recent and
disappointing live-action remake, ranks with Disney's best
feature-length cartoons. Cruella De Vil, the dog-stealing,
fur-coat-wearing, most-wanted poster girl for PETA, is one of
Disney's most heinous villains. And the dogs are adorable.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dead Man on Campus'' _ Dead movie at box office. For those who
believe that no comedy is too moronic to make money, I offer this
corpse as proof that moviegoers aren't as dumb as Hollywood thinks.
Don't get me wrong: Even suicide can be played for comedy if it's
funny. This isn't.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   OSCAR ON VIDEO: ``Saving Private Ryan,'' Steven Spielberg's
multinominated World War II epic, will probably hit video stores in
May, according to Video Business magazine. Universal Home Video
plans to ship between 1.2 million and 1.5 million cassettes, priced
as rentals. That would make it the biggest non-sell-through title
in video history.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 23: ``Pleasantville,'' ``What Dreams
May Come,'' ``Mighty Joe Young,'' ``Firelight,'' ``Bride of
Chucky,'' ``Jerry Springer's Ringmaster,'' ``Carla's Song,'' ``From
Dusk Till Dawn 2,'' ``Strike!'' March 30: ``The Rugrats Movie,''
``Oblomov,'' ``Siberiade,'' ``Home Fries,'' ``Mutual Needs.'' April
6: ``Beloved,'' ``American History X,'' ``A Soldier's Daughter
Never Cries,'' ``I Still Know What You Did Last Summer,'' ``An
Unexpected Life,'' ``Meet Joe Black,'' ``The Dentist 2.'' April 13:
``The Tempest,'' ``Bug Buster,'' ``Ambushed,'' ``Basil,'' ``Detroit
9000,'' ``Conspirators of Pleasure.'' April 20: ``A Bug's Life,''
``Monument Ave.,'' ``Simon Birch,'' ``Apt Pupil,'' ``A Night at the
Roxbury.'' April 27: ``Happiness,'' ``Ground Control.'' May 4:
``Babe: Pig in the City.''
</P>
