A1362 &Cx1f; ttc-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LADN-BUSINESS &LR;      03-15 0255
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Tuesday, March 16, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LA-VALLEY-HOMES (Los Angeles) _ Home sales in L.A.'s San
Fernando Valley plunged nearly 11 percent during February while
prices continued to rise. It's the third consecutive year-over-year
sales drop but analysts say the year's first two months are not
trendsetters by any means. Prices increased 22 percent. By Gregory
J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   HASKEL-SALE (Los Angeles) _ A private investment fund is buying
Haskel International, Inc. for $72.8 million, or $12.90 per share,
a 35 percent premium over Haskel's closing price Friday.
Burbank-based Haskel is one of the world's leading manufacturers of
high-pressure liquid pumps and gas boosters. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   MGM-VIDEO (Los Angeles) (McNary) _ Troubled MGM will pay Warner
Bros. $225 million to regain control of the home video rights to
its movies, nearly a decade after they were sold off to finance
Giancarlo Parretti's ill-fated buyout of the studio. By Dave
McNary.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Let the hire beware. Daily News
columnist Ken Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational
behavior, answers readers' questions on workplace ethics and
relationships.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
