   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MONEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Internal Revenue Service has been
getting the word out that many taxpayers are missing a tax break _
the new child tax credit _ that could sharply cut their tax bill.
If you qualify for this break, which applies if you support a
child, grandchild, stepchild, adopted child or foster child who is
under age 17, it can mean a credit of up to $400 per child. By
PAMELA YIP.
