<P>
   MEDICARE-REPORT (Washington) _ The chairman of Medicare
commission releases final details of its reform plan, which is
intended to win enough votes on 17-member panel that disbands on
Tuesday. By Robert Pear. (The story has moved in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   SMALLPOX-VIRUS (United Nations) _ In a development likely to
have a significant impact on President Clinton's decision on
whether to support plans to destroy the world's last known samples
of smallpox virus, a new scientific report concludes that
preserving the deadly virus may provide important scientific and
medical opportunities that would be lost if the virus were
destroyed. By Judith Miller. (The story has moved in ``a'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stock prices rise sharply, swept higher by a
couple of big merger announcements, enthusiastic buying of
technology shares and an optimistic earnings forecast from UAL
Corp. The advance pushed the Dow Jones industrial average and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index to new records. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
(The story has moved in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
