<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-15 22:06 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1643 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BBA-ANGELS-LADN-(SLAN     03-15 0190
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OLIVARES TRIES TO KEEP SCHEDULE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MESA, Ariz. _ While the rest of his Angels teammates took Monday
off, pitcher Omar Olivares threw to Angels minor-leaguers at Gene
Autry Park in order to maintain his regular throwing schedule.
</P>
<P>
   Olivares has the edge over Jason Dickson and Jarrod Washburn in
the competition for the No. 5 spot in the starting rotation. Last
year, Olivares was effective both in the rotation and the bullpen,
going 9-9 with a 4.03 ERA in 36 games (27 starts).
</P>
<P>
   __ Bound for minors: The Angels optioned five players to the
minor leagues. Pitcher Geoff Edsell, outfielder Norm Hutchins and
catcher Bret Hemphill have been assigned to Triple-A Edmondton;
pitchers Ramon Ortiz and Mark Harriger have been assigned to
Double-A Erie.
</P>
<P>
   __ Debuts: Pitcher Chuck Finley will make his first Cactus
League start of the spring today against the Chicago White Sox in
Tempe at 12:05. Todd Greene will catch the first three innings, his
first action behind the plate this spring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
