<HEADLINE>
PONCHOS CAN'T BE FAR BEHIND 
</HEADLINE>
 (fb) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Winter coat weather persists in many parts of the country, but
thoughts of spring have already stirred fashion-conscious shoppers
to snap up the coming season's cover-up of choice, the poncho.
Stores report that many styles have already sold out, but some are
still in stock.
</P>
<P>
   At Saks Fifth Avenue, there are nylon rain ponchos from Steve by
Searle in black or stone ($225) and from Adrienne Landau in
shocking pink, khaki or black ($275). Bergdorf Goodman has rain
ponchos in black by Isaac Mizrahi ($130), Windcoat ($325) and
Yeohlee ($435).
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has wool ponchos by Julia Hill in tones of pink
or blue ($525) and, in a range of colors, ponchos by Clarissa Webb
($595) and pashminas by William Welstead ($675).
</P>
<P>
   Louis Vuitton has three styles by Marc Jacobs, all in white, in
rubberized cotton or coated silk ($510 and $545).
</P>
</TEXT>
