<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-INDIANS-RESORTS-NYT, which moved
in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``It's like a leisure virus. We're trading our souls for money.
Some tribe members say `Hey, it's OK. It's glamorous.' But that's
not what we are supposed to be. We are supposed to be stewards of
this land.''
</P>
<P>
   _JOSE LUCERO, of the Santa Clara Pueblo tribe, on his objection
to developing a casino resort.
</P>
